^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The line you took depends on your guessing clubs. There is no point in delaying. You are going to have to guess sooner or later anyway. Now having said that, let's discuss the best line of play. Basically Marge, you pinned your hopes on the club suit. Let's say you guess the clubs right. That gives you four clubs, three hearts, and one spade. It is still not enough tricks, you need a diamond trick. You still have to set up a diamond trick. Here is your best hope. You made the very good play of ducking spades for 3 tricks. That was excellent. |
PG| ***** 26 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|You now simply have to hope that whoever has the @DA does not have the last spade. Otherwise you should be down no matter what. Therefore, there is no need to guess the clubs. Simply throw away two small hearts and two small clubs or two clubs, a heart and a diamond in dummy and keep all of dummy's diamonds. Knock out the @DA. If they don't cash the last spade, you have 9 easy tricks without worrying about who has the @CQ. Basically, your plan should be to take enough diamonds to make the contract--at least four.|
