cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As I said, if it is in the wrong place you are going down anyway. So, it has to be in the right place. You don't have 9 tricks otherwise. Now as to the defense given Marge's line. At trick eight Ginny should have played diamond nine instead of six (start of a high/low) to give Mei ann count--not that important here. Mei ann, should win the first or second round of diamonds then play hearts to set the contract. Mei ann had two sure heart tricks.|
