^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, most of my comments are about bidding. I would not open Mei ann's hand, as it does not meet the rule of 20. Ginny's 1H overcall is fine. However, Marge should not bid 1S. Responding to an overcall is different than responding to an opener. Since you double and correct with a real strong hand, overcaller's hand is usually limited to 15 or 16. Therefore, responder to overcaller is not obligated to bid with six points. Now, if responder has support, she should definitely raise, even with six points. But bidding a new suit should show a 5+ card suit.|
PG| ***** 48 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I also play, were Marge an unpassed hand that a new suit is forcing, even as a response to an overcaller. However, some partnerships do not play that. They play 1S can be passed even were Marge an unpassed hand. Marge should bid, but 1N is probably better. In this case 1N does not show 6-10. It tends to show 8- a bad 11 because you can pass with a balanced 6 or 7 count. So, I would have bid 1N with your hand Marge. Remember, Ginny can have as few as 8 or 9 points. Unlike an opener, she does not have to have a good hand. Therefore, responder to an overcaller has to be more careful, particularly with no known fit.|
