^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|What happened on this hand is Marge made a reasonable bid, but spades is a much better contract than NT. My rule in general about 2C is to open with a balanced 22+ because I can rebid 2N, or 3N with 25+.  Otherwise, with a long minor, I see if I can count 9 tricks in my hand. Marge's hand is close: 6 diamonds a club and a spade for sure. But particularly because her suit is diamonds, I would open 1@D.|
