^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Ginny is making at least a mild slam try, and is showing exactly 3 spades. Why is that? Well, first of all, with 4+ spades, Ginny should bid Jacoby 2N right away. So, by not bidding 2N, Ginny is denying 4 spades. 2C by Ginny establishes a game force. And one of the important principles of 2/1 is something known as "fast arrival." Fast Arrival works as follows. Once you establish a game force, the faster you bid game, the less interested you are in slam. Therefore, if Ginny had a min opener with 3 spades, she would bid 4S over 2D--she is "arriving fast" at game.|
