^c@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In general, I recommend against it being suit preference. More often than not, you have no suit preference, and are simply discarding an even card from a long suit in which you are sure the discard will not adversely affect the defense.

On rare occasions, you may discard a high even card to show suit preference for the higher of the remaining suits. But, that opportunity rarely presents itself. I would stick with "odd encourages, even discourages" and that's it.|
